<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-03-17T10:44:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-03-17T10:44:00-05:00" n="439" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d439">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">882.7962/64: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Liberia</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Wharton</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Monrovia</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-03-17T15:00:00-00:44">March 17,
                                    1942—3 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received 3:05 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>83. From McBride. Department’s 53, March 13, 6 p.m. President Barclay
                            assured me today that fullest cooperation will be extended by Liberian
                            health authorities. United States forces will be given full control in
                            defense areas and any contiguous areas they may deem desirable.
                            [McBride.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Wharton</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>